  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Prepared from the buds of the magnolia flower, xinyihua is a warm, bitter herb that enters the lung and stomach meridians to expel wind-cold and relieve nasal congestion, headaches and nasal discharge. It is used to treat conditions including sinusitis and rhinitis.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "辛夷花傳統用作發散風寒藥，《本草綱目》中云：「治頭面目鼻之病。」辛夷花能發散風寒、宣通鼻竅，常用於鼻淵頭痛、風寒頭痛等。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "辛夷花传统用作發散風寒药，《本草綱目》中云：「治头面目鼻之病。」辛夷花能發散風寒、宣通鼻竅，常用于鼻淵头痛、風寒头痛等。\n"
  },
  "tcmHistory": {
    "en": "First appeared in Divine Husbandman's Classic of the Materia Medica.\n",
